            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The block was found on top of the dividing wall between tombs 131 and 132, to be understood as epitymbion for the two tombs. A second small fragmentary block, from the same context, with a blue painted (but not engraved) letter may form part of the same or an associated incription (Fragment b)<!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--block on top of the dividing wall between tombs 131 and 132, to be understood as epitymbion for the two tombs. The inscription incised and painted (red and blue, alternating between letters) is thought to relate probably to the male of  T.131 and reads LEUKADIOS. Traces of letters above also.--></p>
            </div>
